"title": "5821: criticism, amongst believers",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5821: criticism, amongst believers",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Harsh criticism is out of place among believers, who are urged to see each other in the best possible light. Criticism of God arises from a failure to understand his actions and purposes.</p>\n<h2>Criticism forbidden among believers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:9\">JAS 5:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:1-Matt7:5\">MAT 7:1–7:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:37-Luke6:42\">LUK 6:37–6:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:1-Rom14:4\">ROM 14:1–14:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:10-Rom14:13\">ROM 14:10–14:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:10\">1CO 10:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:15\">GAL 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:14-Phil2:16\">PHP 2:14–2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:11-Jas4:12\">JAS 4:11–4:12</a></p>\n<h2>Reacting to criticism</h2>\n<h3>Some criticism can be disregarded</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:21-Eccl7:22\">ECC 7:21–7:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:2-1Cor4:5\">1CO 4:2–4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:16-Col2:18\">COL 2:16–2:18</a></p>\n<h3>Criticism can be dealt with by settling the dispute</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:15\">MAT 18:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:1\">PRO 15:1</a></p>\n<h2>Integrity is a defence against criticism</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:4\">DAN 6:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:20-2Cor8:21\">2CO 8:20–8:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:7-Titus2:8\">TIT 2:7–2:8</a></p>\n<h2>Criticism can be constructive</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps141:5\">PSA 141:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:17\">PRO 10:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:5\">PRO 15:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:6\">PRO 27:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:9\">PRO 27:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:23\">PRO 28:23</a></p>\n<h2>Criticism and complaint directed against God</h2>\n<h3>Criticism of God for his apparent injustice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:26-Deut1:27\">DEU 1:26–1:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:7-Jer20:9\">JER 20:7–20:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah4:1-Jonah4:4\">JON 4:1–4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:1-Hab1:4\">HAB 1:1–1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:12-Hab1:17\">HAB 1:12–1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:13-Mal3:15\">MAL 3:13–3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:19-Rom9:21\">ROM 9:19–9:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:16\">ISA 29:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:9\">ISA 45:9</a></p>\n<h3>Criticism of God for his apparent disregard of his people's plight</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:27\">ISA 40:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:1\">PSA 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps13:1-Ps13:2\">PSA 13:1–13:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:1-Ps22:2\">PSA 22:1–22:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:9-Ps42:10\">PSA 42:9–42:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:23-Ps44:24\">PSA 44:23–44:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:10-Ps74:11\">PSA 74:10–74:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:4-Ps80:6\">PSA 80:4–80:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps108:11-Ps108:12\">PSA 108:11–108:12</a></p>",
